SIMPLE: washer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Washer
<hw>Wash"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>w⟦ae⟧scere</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which,
washes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A ring of metal, leather, or other material, or a
perforated plate, used for various purposes, as around a bolt or screw
to form a seat for the head or nut, or around a wagon axle to prevent
endwise motion of the hub of the wheel and relieve friction, or in a
joint to form a packing, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Plumbing)</fld> <def>A fitting, usually having a
plug, applied to a cistern, tub, sink, or the like, and forming the
outlet opening.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The common raccoon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Washerwoman</er>,
2.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Washerman</ent>⟦br⟧
